com.turn.ttorrent.client.storage

Class FileStorage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.turn.ttorrent.client.storage.FileStorage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ByteRangeStorage, ByteStorage, java.io.Closeable, java.io.Flushable, java.lang.AutoCloseable

    public class FileStorage
extends java.lang.Object
implements ByteRangeStorage
    Single-file torrent byte data storage.

    This implementation of TorrentByteStorageFile provides a torrent byte data storage relying on a single underlying file and uses a RandomAccessFile FileChannel to expose thread-safe read/write methods.

      • read

        public int read(java.nio.ByteBuffer buffer,
       long offset)
         throws java.io.IOException
        Description copied from interface: ByteStorage
        Read from the byte storage.

        Read length bytes at offset offset from the underlying byte storage and return them in a ByteBuffer. This method does NOT call Buffer.flip().

        Specified by:
        read in interface ByteStorage
        Parameters:
        buffer - The buffer to read the bytes into. The buffer's limit will control how many bytes are read from the storage.
        offset - The offset, in bytes, to read from. This must be within the storage boundary.
        Returns:
        The number of bytes read from the storage.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If an I/O error occurs while reading from the byte storage.
